# sqlx checksums migration files by their raw bytes. If a checkout converts
# them to CRLF (Windows core.autocrlf), the checksum differs from a checkout
# that kept LF, and sqlx refuses to start ("migration ... was previously
# applied but has been modified"). Pin them to LF on every platform so the
# on-disk bytes are deterministic regardless of git line-ending settings.
frontend/src-tauri/migrations/*.sql text eol=lf
